import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='fertility', data=data, label='Fertility Rate')
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='life_expect', data=data, label='Life Expectancy')
    
    plt.title('What is the trend of fertility rate and life expectancy over the years?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    max_fertility_country = data.loc[data['fertility'].idxmax()]['country']
    country_data = data[data['country'] == max_fertility_country]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='fertility', data=country_data)
    plt.title('Which country has the highest fertility rate and what is the trend over the years?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
